<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFF8FFC7FF71FC7DFD16FB9B" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FC7DFD71FC67" blockId="16.[151,1436,906,1077]" box="[151,652,942,969]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFF8FFC7FF79FC7DFF14FC67" box="[159,233,943,969]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="62.[151,250,1923,1947]" captionTargetBox="[217,1371,196,1887]" captionTargetId="figure-32@62.[206,1381,181,1899]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURE 9. Eudocima materna group and African Eudocima adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605516/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Figs 9</figureCitation>
: C–D, 19: B, 24: G–I, 30: P, 95: H–I)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFF8FFC7FF71FC01FD16FB9B" blockId="16.[151,1436,906,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
This species with the thinner hindwing marginal band can be diagnosed from the very similar 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FB48FC01FAF0FC42" box="[1198,1293,979,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apata">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FB48FC01FAF0FC42" box="[1198,1293,979,1004]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. apata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as discussed under that species above. The vast range of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFF8FFC7FD6DFC25FCF4FBBE" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[651,777,1015,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="materna">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FD6DFC25FCF4FBBE" box="[651,777,1015,1040]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. materna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes Africa, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF8FFC7FC2AFC25FBF5FBBF" box="[972,1032,1015,1041]" name="India" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">India</collectingCountry>
, the Indoaustralian region up to the Central Pacific and the 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFF8FFC7FE78FBC9FDE1FB9B" box="[414,540,1051,1077]" name="Philippines" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFF8FFC7FDCDFBC9FD1DFB9B" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[555,736,1051,1077]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFF8FFC7FD82FBC9FD68FB9B" box="[612,661,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
